_&quot;Now I want to use **org.slf4j**&quot;_: if you just want to use SLF4j, you can use its Log4j 1.2 binding. I assume you also want to upgrade the logging backend from Log4j 1.2 to Log4j 2.x.

You obtain a compilation error, since [`LoggerConfig`](https://logging.apache.org/log4j/2.x/log4j-core/apidocs/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/config/LoggerConfig.html) does not have a `setThreshold` method. Therefore you must use the other methods at your disposal.

If you just want to remove the console appender use:

```lang-java
        LoggerConfig rootLoggerConfig = configuration.getRootLogger();
        rootLoggerConfig.removeAppender(&quot;Console&quot;);
```

If you want to keep it, but silence it, you need to remove it and add it with a different level:

```lang-java
        LoggerConfig rootLoggerConfig = configuration.getRootLogger();
        Appender consoleAppender = rootLoggerConfig.getAppenders().get(&quot;Console&quot;);
        rootLoggerConfig.removeAppender(&quot;Console&quot;);
        rootLoggerConfig.addAppender(consoleAppender, Level.OFF, null);
```

**Edit**: You need also to replace the line:

```lang-java
LoggerContext loggerContext = (LoggerContext) LogManager.getContext();
```

with

```lang-java
LoggerContext loggerContext = (LoggerContext) LogManager.getContext(false);
```

since (as stated in the Javadoc for `LogManager.getContext()`):

&gt; WARNING - The LoggerContext returned by this method may not be the LoggerContext used to create a Logger for the calling class.

